      "comment": "DONKEY FLY (4) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 3.5 lengths at Ballarat in a handy 22.22. Jumping from the pinch draw but in form and has the ability. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Well placed and can measure up. DASH INTENTION (2) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Sandown over 515m behind Rivers Meet (30.25) in a Grade 5. Great chance to atone. MATILDA ROSE (6) turned in a fair 4th placed finish last time at this track over 435m (24.81). Key runner on best form. MINTER SCORCH (8) put a gap on her rivals last start. Must be respected.",
